        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 1:40PM EDT by NWS Grand Rapids MI</headline>
        <description>At 130 PM EDT...thunderstorms with small hail and the potential to
produce wind gusts over 40 mph had developed over far southwest
Lower Michigan between South Haven and Kalamazoo. This activity was
moving to the east at 30 MPH.

Additional thunderstorms are expected to develop this afternoon
across southern Lower Michigan and move east. Some of these storms
will be capable of small hail and wind gusts approaching 50 MPH.
However, conditions will become more favorable for severe thunderstorms
across south-central and southeast Lower Michigan later this
afternoon with the potential to produce damaging winds.

Stay tuned for the latest information and if skies darken be
prepared to move indoors.
</description>
